<HEADLINE> Blair Congratulates Obuchi Upon Election Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 24 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
Friday congratulated Keizo Obuchi upon his election as president
of Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party.
</P>
<P>
Obuchi, the current foreign minister, is expected to be
designated prime minister by the House of Representatives on July
30 to replace outgoing Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto,
who resigned early this month after a devastating election defeat.
</P>
<P>
Blair was quoted by Reuters as saying Friday afternoon, "I
believe that as a result of the election there will be a very
strong will there in Japan to tackle the problems that can affect
the whole of the world not just Japan."
</P>
<P>
The Japanese economy, the second-biggest in the world, is
sliding into serious recession in decades and political
commentators predict tremendous challenges for the new Japanese
government leader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
