<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Estate Development Regulations Published (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The State Council today
published the Administrative Regulations on the Development and
Operation of Real Estate In Urban Areas in a bid to standardize
and regulate the country's fledgling real estate industry.
</P>
<P>
The regulations consist of six chapters and 43 articles.
</P>
<P>
Under the regulations, real estate development activities cover
the building of infrastructure and housing projects on state-owned
land in planned urban areas, the transfer of real estate projects
under development, and the selling or leasing of commercial
buildings.
</P>
<P>
The development and management of real estate business should
be undertaken in line with the principle of considering economic,
social and environmental consequences, and through working out
overall plans to integrate development and building into a
complete system, according to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
The State Council administrative department in charge of the
construction sector takes charge of the regulatory and
administrative work on the development and operation of real
estate.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors who intend to open real estate companies in
China should not only comply with the requirements for Chinese
nationals in setting up such firms, but also should go through
examination and approval procedures in accordance with the
Investment Law and administrative regulations concerning overseas
funded-enterprises, according to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
The approval of real estate projects should conform to the
requirements of the overall land-use plan, annual plans for the
utilization of land for building, annual outlines for urban
construction, and annual plan for real estate development
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
