<HEADLINE> 860 Firms To Attend China Int'l Aviation, Aerospace Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Over 860 companies from 28
countries and regions are expected to bring their exhibits to the
China International Aviation and Aerospace Exhibition to be
held in Zhuhai City, Guangdong Province, on November 15-22.
</P>
<P>
Yu Rong'ai, deputy mayor of Zhuhai, told a news conference here
today that 120 aircraft will be exhibited.
</P>
<P>
Flying Chinese military squadrons and several from foreign
countries including Russia, Britain, the United States and
Switzerland will also perform during the exhibition, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the second following the one in 1996, is
sponsored by the city government of Zhuhai, the China Civil
Aviation Administration, the China Aviation Industry Corporation,
the China Aerospace Industry Corporation, and the China Council
for the Promotion of International Trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
