<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Estate Development Regulations Published (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The projects should conform to the principle of integrating the
transformation of old urban areas with construction of new urban
areas, and with greater attention attached to districts with poor
infrastructure, traffic and environment, as well as those areas
with a concentration of dilapidated housing or shanties.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, according to the regulations, due attention should
be given to protecting and improving the ecological environment in
urban areas, and protecting historic and cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
Developers should carry out real estate projects in line with
contracts signed on the transfer of land-use rights, regarding the
purpose of the land-use, and the terms set for the projects.
</P>
<P>
Those who fail to begin the project when the first year of the
terms expire must pay some 20 percent of the price to purchase the
rights of land-use. And those who have failed to begin projects
when the second year of the terms expire will be deprived of
land-use rights by the government, without refund.
</P>
<P>
Among other regulations, developers should take responsibility
for the quality of their real estate projects, and a project may
not be put into use before it has passed official appraisal, or it
is determined unqualified by the appraisal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
