<HEADLINE> Shanghai's B-Shares Index Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The market index of B-Shares on
the Shanghai Stock Exchange continued a nosedive this week,
with total transactions in both A-Shares and B-Shares down 20
percent from last week.
</P>
<P>
The index of B-Shares on the Shanghai Exchange finished at
34.87 points today, down 6.09 points from last week. The
total trading in B-Shares also declined by 55 percent this week,
at 71 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Index of the Shanghai Stock Exchange dropped by
1,300 points on the first trading day of this week. However, the
index reported a rebound of 0.92 percent today, the last trading
weekday, to finish at 1,326.82 points.
</P>
<P>
The SSE-30 index, based on 30 blue chips selected from
more than 300 A-Shares for domestic investors on the Shanghai
exchange, closed at 3,314.25 points, an increase of 1.35
percent.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover of treasury bonds reached 39.47
billion yuan, down 6.3 billion yuan from the previous week.
</P>
<P>
The spot-bond turnover was about 11.6 billion yuan,
and bond repurchasing stood at 27.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Only one of the 18 listed stock-trading funds gained this week,
with the other 17 declining.
</P>
<P>
Indexes of industrial enterprises maintained a rising momentum
this week, up 1.19 percent, with real estate indexes down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
