<HEADLINE> Li Lanqing Inspects Henan, Hebei Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
toured Henan and Hebei provinces from July 22 to 24 to discuss
educational and financial issues with local officials.
</P>
<P>
During his trip, Li visited a number of universities and
a major state-owned steel complex.
</P>
<P>
He showed great concern for the housing conditions of
university teachers, especially the younger ones, pledging that
old-style and dangerous residential buildings at universities will
not be brought into the next century.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the government has allocated two billion yuan
to building apartments for university teachers.
</P>
<P>
In talks with provincial leaders, the vice premier also asked
them to work hard to realize the year's economic goals.
</P>
<P>
Greater efforts should be made in the areas of taxation,
anti-corruption and anti-smuggling, he said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the decision of the central government to keep
army, police and law departments out of business
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
