<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze River Flood Peak Passing Through Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The third flood peak of the
Yangtze River has been passing through the worksite of the Three
Gorges Dam area slowly today, with a water flow rate reaching
52,000 cubic meters per second at 20:00 (Beijing Time).
</P>
<P>
Both the diversion channel and shiplock have totally been shut
down, which has stopped navigation in the Three Gorges section of
the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
So far, the navigation has come to a complete halt and the
water level of the river has been on the rise.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the flood peak has not brought any damages to the
Three Gorges Dam project, while the construction of the project is
still proceeding in accordance with the schedule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
