<HEADLINE> 15 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- A total of 15 members of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) had been killed in recent
military operations staged by the Turkish security forces in
southeastern Turkey, an official statement said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the government troops had killed 13 PKK militants
in Yuksekova town of Hakkari province bordering Iran and two in
Hozat town of Tunceli province.
</P>
<P>
However, the statement failed to disclose when the PKK rebels
were killed in the region.
</P>
<P>
In another development, Turkey's Anatolia News Agency reported
Friday that a group of PKK guerrillas opened fire on a military
vehicle near Darende town of Malatya province late Thursday night,
leaving one soldier dead and 10 military personnel wounded.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 14-year-old separatist war in
eastern and southeastern Turkey in a bid to establish an
independent Kurdish state in the region.
</P>
<P>
More than 35,000 people including PKK rebels, government
troops and civilians have been killed in armed conflicts since
then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
