<HEADLINE> OAU Members to Convene Ministerial Conference on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Organization
of African Unity (OAU) from Indian Ocean region and those
neighboring the Federal Islamic Republic of the Comoros,
decided Friday to convene a regional ministerial consultation
conference on Comoros.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the OAU, the decision
was made at a meeting here at the OAU headquarters at the
initiative of OAU Secretary-General Salim Ahmed Salim.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is a follow-up on the decision of the 34th OAU
summit held in Ouagadougou, Burkina Faso last June, with respect
to the situation in Comoros.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, Salim Himidi, Foreign Minister
of the Comoros, briefed the meeting extensively on the prevailing
situation in the country with particular reference to the
instability and crisis in the island of Anjouan.
</P>
<P>
At the end of its deliberations, the meeting encouraged South
Africa, which was mandated by the summit to coordinate the
regional efforts on the Comoros, to make urgently
preparations for the convening of a regional ministerial
consultation conference.
</P>
<P>
South Africa is also urged to examine how best to implement
the decision of the Ouagadougou summit as well as examine all
possible options for facilitating the restoration of normalcy in
the archipelago, the press release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
