<HEADLINE> Afghanistan Urged to Ensure Safety of Humanitarian Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Hennadiy Udovenko,
president of the United Nations General Assembly, Friday called on
parties in Afghanistan to ensure the safety and security of
humanitarian staff in the country.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Udovenko expressed his grave concern over the
recent developments in Afghanistan which seriously undermine
international efforts to provide humanitarian aid to the Afghan
people.
</P>
<P>
The president deplored the killing last weekend of two Afghan
nationals working for the Office of the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugee and the World Food Program.
</P>
<P>
He said he is also distressed by the expulsion of
non-governmental organizations, which were the main partners of
United Nations agencies in the country.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko urged the parties in the country to refrain from any
action that could impede efforts to deliver assistance to the
long-suffering people of Afghanistan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
