<HEADLINE> U.N. to Convene Conference on Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations will
convene a conference on Sierra Leone on July 30, 1998, U.N.
spokesman Fred Eckhard announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The one-day meeting, with the participation of representatives
from the Economic Community of the Western African States and
other countries concerned, will review the situation in the
country and find ways to help the country in its reconstruction
and return and resettlement of the refugees.
</P>
<P>
It will also appeal to the international community to support
the U.N. peacekeeping mission and African peacekeeping forces
operating in the country. 
</P>
