<HEADLINE> U.N. Aid Staff Killed in Burundi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- A U.N. relief staff from
the World Food Program was killed in Burundi's capital Bujumbura,
U.N. Spokesman Fred Eckhard said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
U.N. sources said three armed men entered the U.N. staff's
house late Thursday, subdued the guard on duty and then shot the
relief worker.
</P>
<P>
Executive Director of the World Food program Catherine Bertini
said in a statement that the man had worked extensively in the
Great Lakes region, and his death is the sixth killing this year
of a World Food Program staff member and the third in this month.
</P>
</TEXT>
