<HEADLINE> LIFFE Starts Customers Testing For LIFFE CONNECTtm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The London International Financial
Futures and Option Exchange (LIFFE) announced Friday that it will
start full customer testing for the equity options release of its
new electronic trading platform: LIFFE CONNECTtm on 27 July 1998.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE CONNECTtm is a new generation electronic trading system
which has been designed and developed by the LIFFE.
</P>
<P>
Based on an open architecture and using front-end solutions
developed by a wide range of third party system vendors, LIFFE
CONNECTtm will provide users with the potential to access the
LIFFE market from any PC located anywhere in the world.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first opportunity for the LIFFE'S 45 member
firms, who have signed up to use the service, to test their
in-house systems against the LIFFE's trading engine.
</P>
<P>
The next key step is the start of full dress rehearsals which
will take place over four consecutive weekends prior to the
"go-live" date of 30 November 1998, the LIFFE said.
</P>
<P>
The build for LIFFE CONNECTtm for Futures, which is due to go
live in the second quarter of 1999, is well underway and on
target, according to the exchange.
</P>
<P>
Over 550 people have registered to attend a briefing in London,
to be held by the exchange on Monday 27 July. Software suppliers
and quote vendors who have already agreed to build a front end for
the LIFFE's system will also participate in the event.
</P>
<P>
It was also announced that at the briefing, the LIFFE will
present the key features and benefits of the system to members as
well as announcing that the "go-live" date will be published in
November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
