<HEADLINE> Special Fund Created to Support WHO Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization (WHO)
and the Rockefeller Foundation announced here Friday that the
foundation has created a special Global Health Leadership Fund of
2.5 million U.S. dollars to support the reform process at the WHO.
</P>
<P>
A memorandum of understanding was signed Friday morning in
Geneva by WHO Director-General Dr Gro Harlem Brundtland and the
President of the Rockefeller Foundation Professor Gordon Conway.
</P>
<P>
The non-renewable fund will give Mrs Brundtland, who formally
took office on Tuesday, the financial freedom to recruit top-level
expertise into the organization over the next two years.
</P>
<P>
"WHO is seeking new partnerships with other U.N. agencies,
governmental and nongovernmental organizations, the research
community and the private sector," said Brundtland who used to be
the Norwegian prime minister.
</P>
<P>
"The memorandum we have signed today sends a strong message to
all of them that the change process in WHO is well underway," said
the 59-year-old WHO head.  
</P>
