<HEADLINE> Four People Wounded in Capitol Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Two policemen, a woman tourist
and a suspected gunman were wounded late Friday afternoon in an
exchange of gunfire inside the Capitol at the office of a top
Republican lawmaker, officials said.
</P>
<P>
One man was arrested by a police officer in the office of
Representative Tom DeLay, media reports quoted a spokesman for
DeLay as saying. That officer was wounded, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The shooting on the first floor of the Capitol building
occurred before 4 p.m. EDT, with the House of Representatives in
session and the Senate just finished for the day.
</P>
<P>
"The gunman came into our office and started firing," said John
Feehery, a spokesman for DeLay. Feehery said he heard about 20
shots.
</P>
<P>
Both the officer who stopped the gunman and the gunman were
shot, Feehery said. The congressman, in his office at the time,
was not wounded.
</P>
<P>
Also wounded were a female tourist and another police officer,
said Capitol police Sergeant Dan Nichols. 
</P>
</TEXT>
