<HEADLINE> Taiwan Ass'n Holds Dinner for Visiting Mainland Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIBEI, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Straits Peaceful Reunification
Association hosted a dinner here this evening in honor of the
visiting delegation from the mainland which is here to study
education in the island province of China.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is led by Li Yafei, deputy secretary general of
the mainland's Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Liang Su-Yung, chairman of the Taiwan-based association, said
in a speech at the dinner that pushing exchanges across the
straits and talks between the two associations is a major issue of
concern to the people across the Straits.
</P>
<P>
His association, which was set up in April this year, adheres
to the "one China" principle and hopes that both sides will take
common steps towards a peaceful reunification, Liang noted.
</P>
<P>
The association will give priority to increasing exchanges and
commencing direct mail, communications and air and shipping
services, and to urge negotiations for ending the state of
hostility between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Li extended his gratitude to the Taiwanese association for the
warm reception and remarked that the watchword and orientation of
the mainland association to develop cross-straits relations toward
the peaceful reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
At the present stage, the mainland body has persistently
advocated that cross-straits exchanges be expanded, and further,
that political negotiations across the straits be held as early as
possible. Procedural talks prior to the proposed political
negotiations could held first, he noted.
</P>
<P>
While factors of instability still exist in cross-straits
relations, a stable environment for their development and normal
exchanges between the two sides can only be achieved through
political talks, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He told his host that since people from various circles in
Taiwan have many views and proposals on cross-straits relations
and the issue of the reunification of the motherland, the mainland
association is willing to exchange views with them in order to
join hands in realizing the great cause of reunification at an
earlier date.  
</P>
</TEXT>
