<HEADLINE> Water Level at Jianli Sets Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Latest data from the Ministry of
Water Resources show that the water flow measured at Yichang,
the construction site of the Three Gorges Dam Project, dropped to
50,800 cubic meters per second at 8:00 am today.
</P>
<P>
The water level at Yichang rose to 52.45 meters at 2:00 am
today, with water flow reaching 52,000 cubic meters per second,
while the third flood peak of the Yangtze was passing through the
Three Gorges Dam Project.
</P>
<P>
The water level at the Three Gorges Dam Project has been
receding after the passing of the third flood peak today.
</P>
<P>
However, water levels at Shashi City in Hubei Province and
other areas along the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze have
been rising, by 0.10 to 0.59 meters a day.
</P>
<P>
The water level measured at the Jianli Hydrometric Station
exceeded the record high, approaching 37.2 meters at 6:00 am
today, and it is now rising slowly.
</P>
<P>
The water level of Dongting Lake rose to 34.7 meters, 2.73
meters above the danger line at the Chenglingji Dydrometric
Station at 6:00 am today.
</P>
<P>
The water level of Poyang Lake has also surpassed the danger
line by 2.59 meters, reaching 21.59 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
