<HEADLINE> Hingis Powers Swiss to 1-0 Lead over France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis
powered Switzerland to a 1-0 lead over France in their Fed Cup
world group semifinal on Saturday with a straight-sets victory of
Julie Halard-Decugis.
</P>
<P>
Hingis needed just 67 minutes to romp to a 7-5, 6-1 win
over the 37th-ranked Frenchwoman.
</P>
<P>
Patty Schnyder, winner of back-to-back titles and 14
consecutive matches coming into the tie, was looking to extend her
winning streak and give the Swiss a 2-0 lead when she took on
Amelie Mauresmo later on Saturday. 
</P>
