<HEADLINE> Senior PLA Official Looks to U.S. Military Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAWAII, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The People's Liberation Army of
China (PLA) is willing to further deepen mutual understanding and
strengthen cooperation with the U.S. military, a senior Chinese
military official said.
</P>
<P>
Qian Shugen, PLA deputy chief of general staff, made the
statement Friday while meeting with Admiral Joseph Prueher,
commander-in-chief of the U.S. forces in the Pacific Area.
</P>
<P>
Qian said President Jiang Zemin's successful visit to the
United States last October had helped lift Sino-U.S. relations
into a new stage of development.
</P>
<P>
Prueher said the consensus reached by Jiang and his American
counterpart, President Bill Clinton, on building a constructive
strategic partnership laid a solid foundation for the two
countries, and the two militaries, to further develop their
relations.
</P>
<P>
Qian started his America tour on July 15. 
</P>
