<HEADLINE> Anti-Flood Headquarters Sends Experts to Affected Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The State Flood Control and
Drought Relief Headquarters today sent an expert team, headed by
Deputy Minister of Water Resources Zhang Jiyao, to Wuhan,
capital of Hubei Province, now threatened by the rising waters of
the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
So far, the headquarters and the ministry have jointly sent
four expert teams to help the flood-affected provinces of Hubei,
Anhui, Hunan and Jiangxi.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, five expert teams from the Yangtze River
Water Conservancy Committee have been working along with local
people to protect the dykes along China's longest river. 
</P>
