<HEADLINE> Shanghai Holds 21st Century Management Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Third International
Conference on Management was opened at Shanghai Jiaotong
University here today.
</P>
<P>
About 400 Chinese and overseas management experts attended
today's conference.
</P>
<P>
The conferees will discuss and exchange views on management in
the next century by focusing on 40 special fields of studies.
</P>
<P>
Their topics will include financing and financial management,
intellectual property, restructuring and recreation of
enterprises, strategic management, management of state-owned
businesses, production planning and management, multi-purpose
decision-making, decision analysis, and human resources management.
</P>
<P>
About 100 overseas management experts from 17 countries and
regions are attending the meeting, which will last three days.
</P>
<P>
Amar Bhattachrya of the World Bank, Thomas Byrne from the
U.S.-based Moody's Investors Service, and Lawrence. J. Lau of
Stanford University will lecture on the management of
circulating capital and financial risks control.
</P>
<P>
The conference is co-sponsored by Shanghai Jiaotong University
and the State Natural Science Fund Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
