<HEADLINE> Zhejiang to Begin Work on Highway in Central, Western Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The construction of a highway
which will run through central and western Zhejiang Province will
start soon.
</P>
<P>
According to officials of the provincial planning commission,
construction of the highway was recently approved by the central
government.
</P>
<P>
The 236-kilometer-long highway will start at the provincial capital
of Hangzhou in the north, and extend to Quzhou in the southwest.
</P>
<P>
The highway is expected to be completed in four years, with
a total investment of 6.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the project will have state and local funding,
and will also be provided with government loans from foreign
countries.
</P>
<P>
This new transportation artery will be one section of a
projected State highway from Shanghai in east China
to Ruili in southwest China's Yunnan Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
