<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Secret Ammo Depot Found in Moscow Suburbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Russian law enforcement agents have
found 13 "Shmel" grenade launchers in a clandestine ammunition
depot in Moscow suburbs, Itar-Tass news agency reports.
</P>
<P>
The press center of the Federal Security Department (FSB) said
the launchers, capable of destroying combat hardware and killing
large numbers of people, were spotted near dachas in the Chekhovo
region.
</P>
<P>
Itar-Tass quoted an FSB spokesman as saying the depot, which
belonged to one of the organized criminal gangs operating in the
Moscow region, was discovered by local FSB agents.
</P>
<P>
Since the weapons were hidden in areas where they might have
fallen into the hands of strangers or youngsters, or removed by
criminals, the FSB decided not to wait for the owners to turn up,
the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The weapons were believed to be stolen from army depots and
then sold to organized criminal gangs.
</P>
<P>
Measures are being taken to find the criminals, the FSB
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
