<DOCNO> XIE19980725.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Ministers Call for More Attention to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Maputo Declaration adopted at the end of the conference
Friday , the ministers appealed to the Organization of African Unity
and the African Ministerial Conference on the Environment to consider
the possibility of convening a regional summit in 1999 to raise
awareness and focus attention on issues concerning the
continent's marine and freshwater environment.
</P>
<P>
Africa has over 50 percent significant international river
basins, more than any other continent and with nearly all
countries being part of at least one.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the declaration reiterated the need for the
protection, development and management of shared water resources
through relevant inter-governmental agreements.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also stressed the need for the establishment of
forecasting and warning capabilities of natural disasters at the
regional level.
</P>
<P>
A total of 41 African environment ministers and 12
representatives from other countries attended the meeting held on
July 23 to 24. It has been announced that the next meeting will
be held in Cape Town, South Africa at the end of the coming
November. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
