<HEADLINE> China's Sixth Newspaper Group Established in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Wenhui-Xinmin United Press Group,
China's sixth corporate newspaper group, opened in Shanghai today
in an amalgamation of two leading Chinese newspapers, Wenhui Pao
and Xinmin Evening News.
</P>
<P>
Wenhui Pao has been publishing for 60 years and has an
annual circulation of nearly 500,000 copies. Most of its readers
are Chinese intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
Xinmin Evening News, which will celebrate its 70th
founding anniversary soon, has a daily circulation exceeding 1.8
million copies, first among the 100-odd Chinese evening newspapers.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongwei, president of Wenhui-Xinmin United Press Group,
said today that the combined assets of the two newspapers are
1.74 billion yuan (about 210 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
At present, the two newspapers are publishing 10 newspapers
and periodicals, and their total periodical circulation is
estimated at 2.5 million copies a year.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that the two papers' total income from
advertising reached 760 million yuan in 1997, with profits of more
than 270 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The two newspapers have set up bureaus in 10 foreign countries
and regions and at the United Nations. They have also
published a special edition for readers in the United States.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
