<HEADLINE> French Master Cooks Write About 150 Years of Chocolate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Two French master cooks have
published a book on the 150-year history of chocolate, in memory
of the founding father of chocolate, Victor Auguster Poulain.
</P>
<P>
"Magic of Chocolate" is written by Marie-Christine and
Didier Clement and in particular is aimed at those who love
cooking, and pastry-making amateurs, at home.
</P>
<P>
Published by the Albin Michel publishing house, the book
contains many recipes on making chocolate, such as chocolate
served with clementines and chocolate soup served with mint. It
also includes a story about the life of Poulain and many colored
photos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
