<HEADLINE> Myanmar Minister Urges to Produce More Paddy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Minister for Agriculture and
Irrigation Major-General Nyunt Tin has called on Myanmar peasants
to do their best to produce one billion baskets of paddy (about
20.9 million tons) this year.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by Nyunt Tin Friday at a ceremony of the
conclusion of the on-job land survey and recording course here,
the official newspaper the New Light of Myanmar reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest official statistics, Myanmar's
agriculture grew by 2.9 percent in its output value in the 1997-98
fiscal year ended March despite of floods and drought during the
year in some areas.
</P>
<P>
The paddy production of the country in the fiscal 1997-98 was
17.3 million tons, a little less than that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 17.6 million tons of paddy with 93,100
tons of rice exported in the 1996-97 fiscal year. 
</P>
