<HEADLINE> FINA Delays Decision on De Bruin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Swimming world governing body FINA
Saturday delayed its decision on Ireland's triple Olympic swimming
gold medallist Michelle De Bruin, who was accused of tampering
with a drug test.
</P>
<P>
Gunnar Werner, FINA's honorary secretary, said FINA needed more
time and information before announcing its verdict.
</P>
<P>
De Bruin and her lawyers met for more than three hours with
FINA doping panel members on Friday.
</P>
<P>
FINA also declined to say when a decision may be expected.
</P>
<P>
De Bruin was alleged to have tampered with a urine specimen she
gave on January 10. 
</P>
