<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yangtze Flood Peak Passes Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The high water level measured at
the Three Gorge Dam construction site began receding slowly today,
after the third flood peak on the Yangtze River this year.
</P>
<P>
The flood peak caused no damage at the Three Gorges Dam
Project, and construction is still proceeding on schedule.
</P>
<P>
The flood peak passed through the dam construction site last
night, with the water-flow rate reaching 52,000 cubic meters per
second.
</P>
<P>
Both the diversion channel and shiplock had been completely
shut down, suspending navigation on the Three Gorges section of
the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 1,000 ships stranded at the dam worksite have
been safely brought into port. And some 170,000 passengers from
these ships have also been moved to safety.  
</P>
</TEXT>
