<HEADLINE> New Shipping Line between China, Republic of Korea Opens to Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 25 (Xinhua) -- A luxury passenger-cargo vessel
which sailed from Inchon in the Republic of Korea (ROK) Friday,
arrived in Dandong in northeast China's Liaoning Province today,
officiating the opening of this new line between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
The shipping line is managed by the Dandong International
Shipping Co. Ltd, a Sino-ROK joint venture with a total investment
of two million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The new route is 233 nautical miles long, and the ship makes the
voyage in 17 hours. Named the "Oriental Pearl", the vessel, which
weighs some 11,000 metric tons and can carry 425 passengers, will
sail twice a week between the two cities. 
</P>
