<HEADLINE> 9 Rebels killed, 25 Injured In Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government troops
Saturday killed nine Tamil rebels and injured 25 others in the
north of the country, a military spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said a group of about 70 Tamil rebels who
came by boat had tried to infiltrate into the area by attacking
government troops' bunker line Saturday morning at Gurunagar in
Jaffna district.
</P>
<P>
The troops repulsed the attack with artillery and mortars and
caused heavy casualties to the terrorists.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two soldiers were killed and five others and one
civilian injured during the confrontation, said Dewage, adding
that a search and clear operation is in progress.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government since 1983 for a separate state in the north and east
of the country. 
</P>
