<HEADLINE> 37 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- A total of 37 members of Turkey's
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the past two
days of military operations in southeastern Turkey, the
semi-official Anatolia News agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Turkish security forces on Thursday started the operations
against a group of PKK militants who took shelter near the
Yuksekova town of Hakkari province bordering neighboring Iran.
</P>
<P>
Turkish fighter planes and Cobra helicopters bombarded the
rebel positions to assist the ground troops, said the agency.
</P>
<P>
It added that the military operations were continuing in the
region.
</P>
<P>
More than 35,000 people, including PKK rebels, government
troops and civilians, have been killed in conflicts since the
PKK started a separatist war in 1984 for the establishment of
an independent Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
