<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Buy Russian Helicopters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will purchase two
Russian multi-purpose all-weather helicopters at a cost of 70
million ringgit (about 16.99 million U.S. dollars), according to
Housing and Local Government Minister Ting Chew Peh Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Cabinet has directed that the purchase of the helicopters
for the Fire and Rescue Department be made before the forthcoming
Commonwealth Games which will be held here from September 11 to
21, the minister told reporters in Alor Setar, capital of the
northern state of Kedah, Malaysia's national news agency Bernama
reported.
</P>
<P>
He said the preparations of the specification for the
modification of the MI17 helicopter had been in the final stage.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter which could carry six firemen would be used for
fire-fighting, rescue and cloud-seeding, he said, adding that for
a start, the helicopter would be piloted by Royal Malaysian Air
Force (RMAF) personnel. 
</P>
