<HEADLINE> Nurse Accused of Murdering 30 Patients in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 25 (Xinhua) -- A 28-year-old nurse has been accused
of murdering some 30 elderly patients in a hospital in Mantes-la-
Jolie, a small city in the south of Paris, by practicing
euthanasia on them over the past three years.
</P>
<P>
Christine Malevre, who had admitted the murders, attempted to
commit suicide after she was put under judicial inquiry in early
May, the authorities of Francois Quesnay hospital said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Holder of a state diploma on nursery and having received
excellent evaluations for her work, Malevre was suspected to have
killed elderly patients suffering from mental and lung disorders,
but "their state of health did not leave any doubt about the fatal
end of their diseases," said the hospital.
</P>
<P>
As a nation with a strong Catholic tradition, France has not
legalized euthanasia.
</P>
<P>
The hospital did not notice the abnormal deaths until a patient
died under suspicious circumstances on May 6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
