<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Cyclists and sport's chiefs decided
on Saturday to go on with the Tour de France and to meet at the
end of the season to try to solve the crisis in the sport.
</P>
<P>
Team leaders and French Cycling Federation boss Daniel Baal, who
 is also number two in the International Cycling Union (UCI), met
before the start of the Tour's 13th stage following a protest by
riders on Friday.
</P>
