<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Supports Middle East Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) here Saturday called for the implementation of the
"land for peace" principle in the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN foreign ministers said in a joint communique that they
urged the implementation of all pledges, commitments and
obligations made by the parties under the Oslo Accord and the
Madrid Conference, which significantly stressed the principle of
land for peace.
</P>
<P>
The ministers reaffirmed their support for the Middle East
peace process within the framework of U.N. Resolutions 242, 338
and 425, calling on all parties concerned to ensure the
continuation of negotiations on tracks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministers reiterated their demand that Israel
take immediate steps to stop the building of a new settlement at
Jabel Abu Ghaneim and similar activities in the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
They also condemned the decision of June 21, 1998 by Israel to
expand the border of Jerusalem and extend municipal authority over
a number of Israeli settlements.
</P>
<P>
The ministers called for the revocation of the decision.
</P>
<P>
Israel and Palestine have made little progress in their peace
process since Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu assumed
office. 
</P>
