<HEADLINE> Philippine Rebels Accused of Linkage With Kidnappers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine military on Saturday
accused the secessionist Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) of
"conspiracy" with kidnap-for-ransom groups operating in Central
Mindanao, the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Speaking over a local radio station, Major General Rolando
Bautista, chief of the Army's 6th Infantry Division, chided the
MILF for questionably disclosing kidnap victims' transfer from one
group to another.
</P>
