<HEADLINE> Moderate Daily Solicits Assistance for Convicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The pro-moderate daily Iran
Saturday published a bank account of convicted Tehran Mayor
Gholamhussein Karbaschi for public donations to help him pay the
huge fine imposed by the court.
</P>
<P>
A notice printed in the front page of the English-language
newspaper said those who intended to help Karbaschi pay the fine
can send their donation to the account No. 89700 at the Bank Melli.
</P>
<P>
The daily said the account was published after a large number
of people expressed readiness to help Karbaschi, who was believed
to be a victim of the fierce political struggle between the
conservatives and moderates in the country.
</P>
<P>
Finding Karbaschi guilty of embezzlement and misappropriation
of public funds, an Iranian court Thursday sentenced him to five
years in prison and fined him 1 billion Iran rials (180,000 U.S.
dollars at the market price).
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi refused to comment on the verdict, but his lawyers
said that he would appeal the verdict. Under the law, he will
remain free until he appealed the court verdict.
</P>
<P>
There are have been mixed reactions among the society to the
verdict on Karbaschi. While some said the punishment was unjust or
unexpectedly harsh, the hard-liners claimed that it was too
lenient and they demanded the execution of the former mayor.
</P>
<P>
The case of Karbaschi, a moderate technocrat and close ally of
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami, intensified the factional
struggle between the moderates and the conservatives.
</P>
<P>
The moderates accuse the conservatives of politicizing the case
in an aim to weaken the government of Khatami, who enjoyed strong
support from Karbaschi and his followers since the presidential
elections in May last year.
</P>
<P>
However, the conservatives, who control the judiciary, have
vowed to punish any one violating laws and attacked the moderates
for imposing strong political pressure on the judiciary over the
case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
