<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Exports of Fish to EU Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka exported about 1950 tons
of fish to European Union (EU) in the first five months this year,
increasing six percent as compared with same period last year,
according to Fishers Ministry sources Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Sri Lanka's fish export is growing steadily in
recently years, it earned about 74 million U.S. dollars last year
with a growth of 7.5 percent compared to earnings in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's fish export to the EU accounts for just 10 percent
from the total fish exports of the country. Last year it exported
7,590 tons to the EU.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has effective mechanism and facilities to ensure
production quality, and setting up of an inspection unit is one of
EU's requirements, the sources pointed out. 
</P>
