<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Send 84-Member Team to C'wealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will send an 84-member
team to compete in the 16th Commonwealth Games scheduled to be
held in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, on September 11-21.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi team, participating in the Games for the 6th
occasion, will compete in six disciplines - athletics, aquatics
(swimming), shooting, cricket, hockey (men) and weightlifting -
out of the Games' 15 disciplines of sports. Other disciplines of
the Games are badminton, boxing, cycling, gymnastics, lawn tennis,
netball, rugby, squash and ten-pin bowling.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh contingent, besides 10 officials, is expected to
include 9 participants in athletics, 5 in swimming, 17 in
shooting, 6 in weightlifting, 20 in hockey and 17 in cricket,
media reports here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Alhaj Mokbul Hossain, member of the parliament, has been named
as chief of the mission.
</P>
<P>
The games, the first of its kind to be held in Asia, is schedul
ed to be opened by head of state of Malaysia Yang Dipertuan Agong
Tuanku Jaafar Ibne Almarhum Tuanku Abdul Rahman at the main
stadium of the National Sports Complex.
</P>
<P>
British Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Edward will also attend
the opening gala. The queen, the head of the Commonwealth and
Patron of the Commonwealth Games, is expected to declare the
closure of the Games on September 21.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh won its first Commonwealth gold in shooting in the
14th Games in New Zealand in January 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
