and Agassi plays third-seeded Wayne Ferreira of South Africa who
beat sixth-seeded Vincent Spadea 6-4, 6-7 (3-7), 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Agassi is 6-0 lifetime against Ferreira, and the great player
this season on hardcourts with a 29-5 record.
</P>
<P>
Agassi needed just 56 minutes to finish Lareau, who had seven
double faults, including three straight to open the second set.
</P>
<P>
In another quick match, Draper needed just 50 minutes to defeat
fifth-seeded Filip Dewulf of Belgium 6-3, 6-2. 
