<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Bank of China to Increase Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China will
work out a series of measures to increase input into housing
loans, said Shang Fulin, deputy-governor of the People's Bank of
China recently.
</P>
<P>
His remarks came at a tele-conference on speeding up
construction of residential housing, which was held at Beijing
recently.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, the four state-owned commercial banks'
outstanding of housing loans had reached 274.2 billion yuan (about
34 billion US dollars), increasing by 12.3 billion yuan over early
this year, he said, emphasizing that the bank will adopt measures
as follows to increase housing loans and strengthen its management.
</P>
<P>
First, all commercial banks are required to shift their key
loan-granting field from housing construction to ordinary housing
consumptions and the building of their auxiliary facilities.
</P>
<P>
Second, commercial banks are allowed to grant loans to
ordinary-housing developers who raise no less than 30 percent of
the investment needed by themselves.
</P>
<P>
Third, commercial banks are also allowed to grant loans to
improve auxiliary facilities for the unsalable commodity housing
and encourage developers to increase housing sales by reducing
prices.
</P>
<P>
Forth, housing-loan mangement will be strengthened to ensure no
ordinary housing loans are appropriated for financing other
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
