<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 25 (Xinhua) -- The Zhuhai Airport, which opened
three years ago, expects to achieve balanced revenues and
expenditures during 1998, according to airport authorities.
</P>
<P>
Feng Zhaoming, vice-general manager of the Zhuhai Airport Group
Corp, revealed the company's financial situation.
</P>
<P>
The airport sustained losses of over seven million yuan (843,300
US dollars) in 1996, but effectively reduced the figure to two
million yuan in the following year. The airport has since placed
priority on directly linking expenditures to revenues.
</P>
<P>
The airport in Guandong Province offers over 100 flights per
week to some 37 Chinese cities.  
