<HEADLINE> Rios Beats Becker for Semifinals in Stuttgart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Marcelo Rios defeated German
veteran Boris Becker in straight sets to reach the semifinals of
the 1.04 million U.S. dollars Mercedes Cup tennis tournament in
Stuttgart on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rios who ranked second only behind Pete Sampras in the ATP
rankings, knocked the 30-year-old Becker out with a 6-2, 6-0 rout
in just 45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Rios will climb to the top of the rankings if he can beat fifth
seed Karol Kucera to reach the final on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The victory was a revenge for the 22-year-old Chilean who lost
to Becker in the semifinals of the Swiss Open in Gstaad earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
Becker, a six-time Grand Slam champion, was still looking for
the first clay court title in his 15-year career after winning 49
of the 250 international tournaments he has played since 1983.
</P>
<P>
French Open champion Carlos Moya, who is seeded two here, beat
Spanish compatriot Fernando Vicente 3-6, 6-3, 6-2 to secure a spot
in the semifinals, where he will face Brazil's Gustavo Kuerten,
who beat Spain's Albert Costa 7-5, 6-0. 
</P>
