<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Laid-Off Workers Ensured of Expenses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Living expenses will be provided
to all laid-off workers and every retiree will get their pensions
paid through a new unified old-age pension system, which is
expected to be introduced nationwide within three months,
according to an ongoing national conference.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily said all retired workers, no matter what
their former employers' present financial status, will start
getting their pensions from a social public pension fund,
beginning August 1.
</P>
<P>
All the country's laid-off workers, discharged because of the
ongoing State enterprise reform to cut redundancy, will be
accommodated in re-employment centers by the end of September,
said Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo at a conference here yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Sources of the conference, which is being attended by the
country's provincial officials in charge of the employment and
social welfare system, revealed that so far 8.2 billion yuan (987
million US dollars) of pension funds have been misappropriated,
causing delays in pension payments to some 1.08 million people.
</P>
<P>
Wu said such irregularities must be thoroughly checked, and
re-employment centers should be set up in every enterprise which
has laid-off workers.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, there were 7.1 million laid-off workers
nationwide, and about a quarter of them have been absorbed into
re-employment centers.
</P>
<P>
The plan was created in Shanghai in 1996 and spread throughout
the country in 1997. Laid-off workers sign three-year contracts
with the centers, which will pay them minimum living expenses,
pension and medicare insurance that come to a total of 3,000 yuan
a year per person.
</P>
<P>
The money is contributed equally by the government, enterprises
and society. Society may offer donations and unemployment
insurance for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
The old-age pension network will eventually expand to cover
workers of enterprises of all ownerships, including private
enterprises and joint ventures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
