further consolidated at the summit, though there is still much
to be done to achieve it.
</P>
<P>
In a global trend of integration and cohesion, the EU favors a
Latin America moving that direction, said the president.
</P>
<P>
The European Parliament proposed the dialogue to reduce the
differences so as to secure the biggest benefit possible for the
economic sectors of the two sides, said Gil Robles.
</P>
<P>
Ibero-America groups the Spanish and Portuguese-speaking
nations in Latin America and Spain and Portugal. 
