<HEADLINE> Thailand's Foreign Reserves increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BANGKOK, July 25(Xinhua) -- Thailand's foreign reserves rose
to 27.2 billion U.S. dollars of July 17, compared with 26.8
billion on July 10, according to figures released by the Bank of
Thailand available Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The bank explained that 20 million of the increase came
through drawings on 17.2 billion U.S. dollar International
Monetary Fund credit line.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 380 million U.S. dollars increase was due to
capital inflows.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, net forward obligations in foreign exchange markets
were unchanged at 12.3 billion U.S. dollars, the Bank said.
