<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Foreign-Funded Enterprises Increasing Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's foreign-funded
enterprises have made major contributions to the city's imports
and exports, with 7.87 billion U.S. dollars worth in the first
half of this year.
</P>
<P>
That accounted for 61.7 percent of the city's total in the
first half, according to Shanghai Customs, which says that foreign
trade by foreign-funded enterprises in the first half was up 14.9
percent on a year-on-year basis.
</P>
<P>
Exports of foreign-funded ventures amounted to 3.44 billion US
dollars, an increase of 535 million US dollars from the same period
last year, and although exports to Asian markets were down in the
past few months, business with Europe, North America, and Latin
America was up by a big margin.
</P>
<P>
Imports of foreign-funded enterprises were also up 12.3
percent, at 4.43 billion US dollars, most of them rolled steel,
telecommunications, integrated circuit, micro-electronics, and
data-processing equipment. 
</P>
