<HEADLINE> Yugoslavian Soccer Coach Offers Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's national coach
Slobodan Santrac offered his resignation on Friday after his soccer squad
failed to make the last eight in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia was beaten 1-2 in the second round of the World Cup by the
Netherlands, losing semifinalist, in Toulouse's Stade Municipal on June 29.
</P>
<P>
