<HEADLINE> More Foreign Funds For Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 25 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Beijing had
been increasing during the first half of the year in spite of the
financial crisis in Asia.
</P>
<P>
During that period, Beijing approved 329 overseas-funded
enterprises, with more than one billion U.S. dollars in
investment, up 30.4 percent over the same period last year,
according the city foreign trade and economic cooperation
committee.
</P>
<P>
The increase is attributed to the city's preferential policies
that improve investment environment and the many multinationals
investing in projects in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, it had 5,245 overseas-funded enterprises,
with 20.9 billion yuan (2.51 billion U.S. dollars) in industrial
output value, up 19 percent from the first five months of last
year, and which paid 2.3 billion yuan in taxes, an increase of
59.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, 148 of the top 500 corporations in the
world had invested in Beijing.  
</P>
