<HEADLINE> China's Largest LPG Low-temperature Storage Base Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 25 (Xinhua) -- China's largest low-temperature
storage base for liquefied gas was completed recently in the
Shenzhen Special Economic Zone in south China.
</P>
<P>
The 99.7-million-U.S.-dollar facility is located on Dapeng
Bay. It has an annual storage capacity of 960,000 tons. It is
mainly designed to store low-temperature liquefied petroleum gas
transported by ocean-going carriers and to turn it into normal
atmospheric temperature LPG to supply neighboring markets.
</P>
<P>
It was built by investors from Shenzhen, Hong Kong and
Japan.  
