<HEADLINE> Greece Pledges to Help Revive Olympic Truce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Greece adhered to its pledge of
helping to revive the Olympic truce made during Athens' bid to
host the 2004 summer games, a Greek official said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to permanent representatives of over 70 United Nations
member-states near Athens, Greek Alternate Foreign Minister George
Papandreou said that the truce honoured during the Olympic games
in antiquity provided a mechanism for mediation and conflict
resolution.
</P>
