<DOCNO> XIE19980725.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany's DASA Seeks Single European Aerospace Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Daimler-Benz Aerospace AG
(DASA) confirmed Friday that it has held talks with other European
aerospace companies to seek the creation of a single European
aerospace company.
</P>
<P>
In response to a report in the Friday edition of the British
Financial Times saying that DASA was in merger talks with British
Aerospace (BAe), a DASA spokesman said Friday that the talks had
taken place, but it also involved other European aerospace
companies.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman stressed that his company wanted to see a wider
European consolidation, not just a bilateral merger with BAe.
</P>
<P>
It has been speculated long ago that DASA and BAe wanted to
push for a pan-European aerospace company first through a
bilateral merger.
</P>
<P>
DASA chairman of the board, Manfred Bischoff, was quoted by
German press as saying recently that it was necessary for leading
European companies to merger themselves into a single European
Aerospace and Defense Company in order to compete with their U.S.
rivals.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested that the possible single European entity also
integrate activities of the current four-European-nation Airbus
consortium.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980725.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Mixed in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar settled mixed in
New York Friday in light trading against major foreign currencies
under the influence of the wild movement on the Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Traders said the dollar came under heavy selling pressure early,
falling to an intraday low of 140.23 Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, analysts said the dollar was pressured against most
European currencies after the Bundesbank hinted at higher interest
rates in the second half of the year.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar eased to 1.7795 German marks
from 1.7851 late Thursday but rose slightly to 141.38 Japanese yen
from 141.33.
</P>
<P>
The British pound rose to 1.6592 U.S. dollars from 1.6531 U.S.
dollars, while the U.S. dollar rose against Canadian dollars to 1.4986
U.S. dollars from 1.4957 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Against other currencies, the dollar dipped to 1.4950 Swiss francs
from 1.5060, to 5.9675 French francs from 5.9870 and to 1,754.00
Italian lire from 1,761.00.  
</P>
</TEXT>
