<HEADLINE> Police Officer Dies from Injury in Capitol Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 24 (Xinhua) -- Two policemen, a woman tourist
and a suspected gunman were shot late Friday afternoon in an
exchange of gunfire just inside the Capitol near the office of a
ranking Republican lawmaker, officials said.
</P>
<P>
CNN reported one of the police officers had died.
</P>
<P>
The gunman had entered through an entrance on the east side of
the Capitol, said police spokesman Dan Nichols. The man's weapon
set off a metal detector, and shots then rang out between the
gunman and at least one police officer, according to a lawmaker's
aide.
</P>
<P>
The shooting on the first floor of the Capitol building, near
the office of Representative Tom DeLay, occurred about 3:40 p.m.
EDT, as the House of Representatives was in session and the Senate
just finished for the day, Media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Also wounded were a female tourist and another police officer.
</P>
</TEXT>
